<SVGAttributeStyle>
<summary>
The <strong><c>style</c></strong> attribute allows to style an element using <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/CSS">CSS</see> declarations. It functions identically to <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes/style">the <c>style</c> attribute in HTML</see>.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>You can use this attribute with any SVG element.</para>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/SVGElementstyle">style</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes/style">HTML <c>style</c> attribute</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/SVG/Attribute/style"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
</SVGAttributeStyle>
